Getting started with SGPdata

Damian W Betebenner

2017-06-30

Introduction

The SGPdata package contains 4 examplar data set for use with student growth percentile (SGP) analyses. One of the data sets, sgpData, specifies the proper format for use with the lower level SGP functions studentGrowthPercentiles and studentGrowthProjections.

WIDE data format: sgpData

The data set sgpData is an anonymized, panel data set comprisong 5 years of annual assessment data in WIDE format. This exemplar data set specifies the format for data used with the lower level studentGrowthPercentiles and studentGrowthProjections functions.

> head(sgpData)
       ID GRADE_2013 GRADE_2014 GRADE_2015 GRADE_2016 GRADE_2017 SS_2013 SS_2014 SS_2015 SS_2016 SS_2017
1 1000185         NA         NA         NA         NA          7      NA      NA      NA      NA     520
2 1000486          3          4          5          6          7     524     548     607     592     656
3 1000710          8         NA         NA         NA         NA     713      NA      NA      NA      NA
4 1000715         NA         NA          4          5          6      NA      NA     469     492     551
5 1000803         NA          5         NA         NA         NA      NA     558      NA      NA      NA
6 1000957          5          6          7          8         NA     651     660     666     663      NA

Use of sgpData for SGP calculations is covered more extensively in the SGP Documentation. However a simple example illustrates how sgpData is supplied to the studentGrowthPercentiles function.

> sgp_g4 <- studentGrowthPercentiles(
        panel.data=sgpData,
        sgp.labels=list(my.year=2015, my.subject="Reading"),
        percentile.cuts=c(1,35,65,99),
        grade.progression=c(3,4))

LONG data format: sgpData_LONG

The data set sgpData_LONG is an anonymized, panel data set comprisong 5 years of annual assessment data in LONG format. This exemplar data set specifies the format for data used with the higher level functions abcSGP, prepareSGP, analyzeSGP, combineSGP, summarizeSGP, visualizeSGP, and outputSGP
